DATATYPE.Description: A very small integer. The signed range is -128 to 127. The unsigned range is 0 to 255.
A small integer. The signed range is -32768 to 32767. The unsigned range is 0 to 65535.
A medium-size integer. The signed range is -8388608 to 8388607. The unsigned range is 0 to 16777215.
A normal-size integer. The signed range is -2147483648 to 2147483647. The unsigned range is 0 to 4294967295.
A normal-size integer. The signed range is -2147483648 to 2147483647. The unsigned range is 0 to 4294967295.
A large integer. The signed range is -9223372036854775808 to 9223372036854775807. The unsigned range is 0 to 18446744073709551615.
A small (single-precision) floating-point number. Cannot be unsigned. Allowable values are -3.402823466E+38 to -1.175494351E-38, 0, and 1.175494351E-38 to 3.402823466E+38.
A small (single-precision) floating-point number. Cannot be unsigned. Allowable values are -3.402823466E+38 to -1.175494351E-38, 0, and 1.175494351E-38 to 3.402823466E+38.

A normal-size (double-precision) floating-point number. Cannot be unsigned. Allowable values are -1.7976931348623157E+308 to -2.2250738585072014E-308, 0, and 2.2250738585072014E-308 to 1.7976931348623157E+308.
This is a synonym for DOUBLE.
This is a synonym for DOUBLE.
An unpacked floating-point number. Cannot be unsigned. Behaves like a CHAR column.
This is a synonym for DECIMAL.
A date. The supported range is \a1000-01-01\a to \a9999-12-31\a.
A date and time combination. The supported range is \a1000-01-01 00:00:00\a to \a9999-12-31 23:59:59\a.
A timestamp. The range is \a1970-01-01 00:00:00\a to sometime in the year 2037. The length can be 14 (or missing), 12, 10, 8, 6, 4, or 2 representing YYYYMMDDHHMMSS, ... , YYYYMMDD, ... , YY formats.
A time. The range is \a-838:59:59\a to \a838:59:59\a.
A year in 2- or 4-digit format (default is 4-digit).

A fixed-length string (1 to 255 characters) that is always right-padded with spaces to the specified length when stored. values are sorted and compared in case-insensitive fashion according to the default character set unless the BINARY keyword is given.
A variable-length string (1 to 255 characters). Values are sorted and compared in case-sensitive fashion unless the BINARY keyword is given.
This is a synonym for CHAR(1).
This is a synonym for CHAR(1).
A column maximum length of 255 (2^8 - 1) characters. Values are sorted and compared in case-sensitive fashion.
A column maximum length of 65535 (2^16 - 1) characters. Values are sorted and compared in case-sensitive fashion.
A column maximum length of 16777215 (2^24 - 1) characters. Values are sorted and compared in case-sensitive fashion.
A column maximum length of 4294967295 (2^32 - 1) characters. Values are sorted and compared in case-sensitive fashion.

A column maximum length of 65535 (2^16 - 1) characters.
A column maximum length of 16777215 (2^24 - 1) characters.
A column maximum length of 4294967295 (2^32 - 1) characters.
An enumeration. A string object that can have only one value, chosen from the list of values.
A set. A string object that can have zero or more values, each of which must be chosen from the list of values.

QUERYRECORD.SQLText: SELECT * \nFROM location\nORDER BY id_location
SELECT * \nFROM type\nORDER BY id_type
SELECT * \nFROM node\nORDER BY id_node
SELECT * \nFROM link\nORDER BY id_link
SELECT * \nFROM interface\nORDER BY id_interface
SELECT * \nFROM channel\nORDER BY id_channel

SELECT n.id_node as id_node, n.description as node_description, i.id_interface as id_interface, d.description as device_description
FROM node n, interface i , device d, link l
WHERE n.id_node = i.id_node AND i.id_device = d.id_device AND l.id_link = \a2\a AND ((l.id_src_interface = \a14\a OR l.id_dst_interface = \a14\a) AND NOT (l.id_src_interface = l.id_dst_interface))
ORDER BY n.description
SELECT * \nFROM section\nORDER BY id_section

SELECT i.id_interface as id_interface, n.description as node_description, d.description as device_description\nFROM interface i, node n, device d\nWHERE i.id_node = n.id_node AND i.id_device = d.id_device
SELECT *\nFROM interface i, node n, device d\nWHERE i.id_node = n.id_node AND i.id_device = d.id_device
SELECT \nFROM interface i, node n, device d\nWHERE i.id_node = n.id_node AND i.id_device = d.id_device

SELECT l.id_link as id_link, l.id_src_interface as id_src_interface, l.id_dst_interface as id_dst_interface, n1.description as src_node_description, n2.description as dst_node_description, d1.description as src_device_description, d2.description as dst_device_description\nFROM interface i, node n, device d\nWHERE i.id_node = n.id_node AND i.id_device = d.id_device

SELECT l.id_link as id_link, l.id_src_interface as id_src_interface, l.id_dst_interface as id_dst_interface, n1.description as src_node_description, n2.description as dst_node_description, d1.description as src_device_description, d2.description as dst_device_description\nFROM link l, interface i1, interface i2, node n1, node n2, device d1, device d2\nWHERE l.id_src_interface = i1.id_interface AND l.id_dst_interface = i2.id_interface AND i1.id_node = n1.id_node AND i2.id_node = n2.id_node AND i1.id_device = d1.id_device AND i2.id_device = d2.id_device

SELECT *\nFROM link l, interface i1, interface i2, node n1, node n2, device d1, device d2\nWHERE l.id_src_interface = i1.id_interface AND l.id_dst_interface = i2.id_interface AND i1.id_node = n1.id_node AND i2.id_node = n2.id_node AND i1.id_device = d1.id_device AND i2.id_device = d2.id_device
SELECT *\nFROM link l, interface i1, interface i2, node n1, node n2, device d1, device d2\nWHERE l.id_src_interface = i1.id_interface AND l.id_dst_interface = i2.id_interface

SELECT *
FROM link l1 INNER JOIN interface i1, link l2 INNER JOIN interface i2, node n
WHERE l1.id_src_interface = i1.id_interface AND l2.id_dst_interface = i2.id_interface AND l1.id_link = l2.id_link AND i1.id_node = n.id_node AND i2.id_node = n.id_node

SELECT *
FROM link l1 INNER JOIN interface i1, link l2 INNER JOIN interface i2, node n
WHERE l1.id_src_interface = i1.id_interface AND l2.id_src_interface = i2.id_interface AND l1.id_link = l2.id_link AND i1.id_node = n.id_node AND i2.id_node = n.id_node

SELECT l1.id_link as id_link, l1.id_src_interface as id_src_interface, l1.id_dst_interface as id_dst_interface
FROM link l1 INNER JOIN interface i1, link l2 INNER JOIN interface i2, node n
WHERE l1.id_src_interface = i1.id_interface AND l2.id_src_interface = i2.id_interface AND l1.id_link = l2.id_link AND i1.id_node = n.id_node AND i2.id_node = n.id_node

SELECT l1.id_link as id_link, l1.id_src_interface as id_src_interface, l1.id_dst_interface as id_dst_interface, 
FROM link l1 INNER JOIN interface i1, link l2 INNER JOIN interface i2, node n
WHERE l1.id_src_interface = i1.id_interface AND l2.id_src_interface = i2.id_interface AND l1.id_link = l2.id_link AND i1.id_node = n.id_node AND i2.id_node = n.id_node

SELECT *
FROM link l1 INNER JOIN interface i1 , link l2 INNER JOIN interface i2
WHERE l1.id_src_interface = i1.id_interface AND l2.id_src_interface = i2.id_interface AND l1.id_link = l2.id_link

SELECT n.id_node as id_node, n.description as node_description, i.id_interface as id_interface, d.description as device_description
FROM node n, interface i , device d, link l
WHERE n.id_node = i.id_node AND i.id_device = d.id_device AND l.id_link = \a2\a AND ((l.id_src_interface = \a14\a OR l.id_dst_interface = \a14\a) AND NOT (l.id_src_interface = l.id_dst_interface))
ORDER BY n.description
